  "planContent": "# 🏗️ Architecture Blueprint\n\n## App Overview\nA high-fidelity video viewing portal replicating the \"Kinetic Editorial\" aesthetic. The application provides a focused, immersive video consumption experience, complete with an interactive video player, metadata display, social engagement controls, and a dynamic sidebar for discovery, optimized for both desktop and mobile platforms.\n\n## Core Features\n- **Video Player**: Centralized interactive player with progress tracking, playback controls (play/pause, skip, volume, settings, fullscreen), and overlay gradients.\n- **Content Metadata**: Displays title, channel info, subscriber count, view counts, and timestamps.\n- **User Engagement**: Actionable buttons for Subscribe (toggle state), Like/Dislike (segmented control), Share, and Save (Download).\n- **Comment System**: Interactive input field for adding comments and a scrollable list of rendered user comments with like/reply capabilities.\n- **Sidebar Navigation**: \"Up Next\" list with category chips, autoplay toggle, and thumbnail-based video recommendations.\n- **Responsive Navigation**: Desktop top-bar with search/profile and mobile-optimized bottom navigation drawer.\n\n## UI & Layout Strategy\n- **Layout type**: Two-column responsive grid (main content + sidebar).\n- **Header**: Fixed top app bar containing the \"Kinetic Editorial\" wordmark, search trigger, and profile avatar.\n- **Main content area**: Left column hosts the video player and detailed metadata; right column hosts the \"Up Next\" list.\n- **Controls**: Primary action buttons (subscribe, like, share) using rounded-full pills; player controls integrated into a gradient overlay.\n- **Footer**: Mobile-only bottom navigation bar with icons for Home, Shorts, Subscriptions, and Library.\n- **Design System**: Tailwind CSS (Primary: #bc0100, Surface: #f9f9f9, Surface-Container: #e2e2e2).\n- **Color scheme**: Kinetic Editorial palette (Red/Surface/Zinc).\n- **Responsive strategy**: Stacked single-column on mobile (content first, then sidebar); side-by-side grid (1400px breakpoint).\n- **Animations & UX**: Tailwind transitions on hover (scale-105, bg-color changes).\n- **Touch Targets**: 44px min-height for all nav icons and primary CTA buttons.\n- **Accessibility**: Use `aria-label` for all icon-only buttons, maintain focus rings (`focus:ring-2`), and ensure high contrast text against backgrounds.\n\n## Data Model & State\n| Variable | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| isPlaying | Boolean | false | Controls play/pause state |\n| currentTime | Number | 0 | Current video timestamp |\n| isSubscribed | Boolean | false | Channel subscription toggle |\n| comments | Array | [] | Collection of comment objects |\n| activeTab | String | 'All' | Selected chip in the sidebar |\n| likes | Number | 128000 | Like count |\n\n- **Persistence Strategy**: Use `window.forge.db.set('video_state', 'metadata', { isSubscribed, likes })`.\n\n## Technical Stack & Libraries\n- **Required CDNs**: Tailwind CSS (CDN), Material Symbols Outlined (Google Fonts), Inter Font (Google Fonts).\n- **Allowed**: Tailwind CSS, Lucide Icons (as fallback/supplemental).\n- **APIs**: None (Static assets and mock data).\n\n## Implementation Steps\n1. Initialize the HTML shell with the provided Meta tags and Tailwind CDN configuration.\n2. Build the Fixed Header component and the Mobile Bottom Navigation component.\n3. Construct the Main Grid container (Desktop `lg:flex` layout).\n4. Implement the Video Player container with absolute positioning for the progress bar and controls.\n5. Create the Video Information metadata section (Title, Channel, Buttons).\n6. Build the Comment Section layout (Input bar and dynamic list).\n7. Implement the Sidebar (Up Next) with fixed-width constraints and overflow control.\n8. Add interactivity (Toggle `isPlaying`, `isSubscribed`, and like/comment state) using Vanilla JS.\n9. Verify responsive stacking behavior: move sidebar to bottom on screens < 1024px.\n10. Finalize touch targets and hover states for all primary interactive elements.\n\n## Edge Cases & Error Handling\n- **Empty State**: Show placeholder imagery/text if comments or recommendations fail to load.\n- **Overflow**: Ensure long video titles use `line-clamp-2`.\n- **Loading**: Use aspect-ratio containers (`aspect-video`) to prevent content layout shift during thumbnail loading.\n- **Validation**: Ensure comment inputs are trimmed of whitespace before updating the state array.",
  "currentHTML": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <meta name=\"referrer\" content=\"no-referrer\">\n    <title>Search - The Kinetic Editorial</title>\n    <script src=\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com?plugins=forms,container-queries\"></script>\n    <script src=\"/forge.js\"></script>\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:wght,FILL@100..700,0..1&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <script>\n        tailwind.config = {\n            theme: {\n                extend: {\n                    colors: {\n                        primary: \"#bc0100\",\n                        secondary: \"#5f5e5e\",\n                        surface: \"#f9f9f9\",\n                        \"on-surface\": \"#1a1c1c\",\n                        \"surface-container-highest\": \"#e2e2e2\",\n                        \"surface-container-low\": \"#f3f3f3\",\n                        \"outline-variant\": \"#ebbbb4\"\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    </script>\n    <style>\n        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }\n        .material-symbols-outlined { font-variation-settings: 'FILL' 0, 'wght' 400, 'GRAD' 0, 'opsz' 24; }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"bg-surface text-on-surface min-h-screen flex flex-col\">\n\n<header class=\"fixed top-0 w-full flex justify-between items-center px-4 py-3 bg-surface/70 backdrop-blur-xl z-50\">\n    <div class=\"flex items-center gap-3 w-full\">\n        <button class=\"p-2 hover:bg-zinc-100 rounded-full transition-colors active:scale-95\">\n            <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined text-on-surface\">arrow_back</span>\n        </button>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 relative\">\n            <input id=\"searchInput\" class=\"w-full bg-zinc-200 border-none rounded-full py-2.5 px-5 text-on-surface focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary/20 placeholder:text-secondary text-base\" placeholder=\"Search The Kinetic Editorial\" type=\"text\"/>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"p-2 hover:bg-zinc-100 rounded-full transition-colors active:scale-95\">\n            <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined text-on-surface\">mic</span>\n        </button>\n    </div>\n</header>\n\n<main class=\"flex-1 pt-20 pb-24 px-6 overflow-y-auto\">\n    <section class=\"mb-10\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary mb-6\">Trending Topics</h2>\n        <div id=\"trendingGrid\" class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-3\"></div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section class=\"space-y-4\">\n        <div class=\"flex justify-between items-center mb-6\">\n            <h2 class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary\">Recent Searches</h2>\n            <button onclick=\"clearHistory()\" class=\"text-primary font-bold text-xs uppercase hover:underline\">Clear All</button>\n        </div>\n        <div id=\"historyList\"></div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section class=\"mt-12 mb-8\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary mb-6\">Discover Curated Sets</h2>\n        <div id=\"curatedGrid\" class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\"></div>\n    </section>\n    \n    <div class=\"text-center mt-8\">\n        <button onclick=\"exportCSV()\" class=\"text-xs font-bold text-primary underline\">Export Recent Searches CSV</button>\n    </div>\n</main>\n\n<nav class=\"fixed bottom-0 left-0 w-full z-50 flex justify-around items-center pt-3 pb-6 px-4 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-2xl shadow-[0_-4px_40px_rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] rounded-t-3xl\">\n    <a class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 font-medium uppercase tracking-widest hover:text-primary transition-colors\">\n        <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined mb-1\">home</span><span class=\"text-[10px]\">Home</span>\n    </a>\n    <a class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 font-medium uppercase tracking-widest hover:text-primary transition-colors\">\n        <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined mb-1\">video_library</span><span class=\"text-[10px]\">Shorts</span>\n    </a>\n    <a class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 font-medium uppercase tracking-widest hover:text-primary transition-colors\">\n        <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined mb-1\">subscriptions</span><span class=\"text-[10px]\">Subs</span>\n    </a>\n    <a class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 font-medium uppercase tracking-widest hover:text-primary transition-colors\">\n        <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined mb-1\">video_settings</span><span class=\"text-[10px]\">Library</span>\n    </a>\n</nav>\n\n<script>\n    const state = {\n        history: [\"Kinetic Motion Design 2024\", \"Minimalism in Digital Media\", \"Best Cinematic Cameras under $2000\", \"Future of AI Editorial\"],\n        trending: [\n            { icon: \"music_note\", label: \"Music\" },\n            { icon: \"sports_esports\", label: \"Gaming\" },\n            { icon: \"newspaper\", label: \"News\" },\n            { icon: \"movie\", label: \"Movies\" },\n            { icon: \"palette\", label: \"Fashion\" }\n        ],\n        curated: [\n            { title: \"Electronic Resonance\", category: \"Editor's Pick\", img: \"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida-public/AB6AXuA-D6Vr441o_TlnaHp6K4tbKORYn_EW8yBaLX986x7PoFAeK5xpoNGoH_dbo0ljsfxiciWFh8kQQYX7xOrtOBxs1i4kyExbGSUJQsCT_9Tyf01xefLo8Y8ZNZ-HASZ_2-hFeXXbM0I493pWfeM6wutW5MZPEI2PCrDsDkF56Qee9vfgXgUbbTPlpV7nQ9GUKc8A1LiVw-ysgR6diBfIorrLRpLYkjrQNWoXMPBa5X93tjFJmhag_bV-VLOkSFmJuWITbjFxin7m9hY\" },\n            { title: \"The Competitive Edge\", category: \"Trending\", img: \"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aida-public/AB6AXuCRI4tji38gC0hcyrFn-M4Di60Tb4b9bGvY2Am998Bszfd-qVRM44P5Mv8wsmlJX8i7di0r8iIzOfDReW-dR5KPS-_9bBKJIavcMVNmaRRgXWbs3cBQ7IJ7taT4cUjcVw2iiKNLCz7MQOcuS9P8JazjpYaeLVZCZDE4I4OLJHHjGdMKMmL18rJl_SDIlJovqZm2thptFNpXPH6tB3CtIq0WaEuGJT2v8H1Ips5pI51-9OOb6TNuGbjD8t_60o9IASSb_HzYr1czZRE\" }\n        ]\n    };\n\n    async function init() {\n        let db = await window.forge.db.get('kinetic_editorial_search', 'default') || state;\n        \n        document.getElementById('trendingGrid').innerHTML = db.trending.map(t => `\n            <div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-surface-container-highest rounded-full hover:bg-on-surface hover:text-white transition-all cursor-pointer group\">\n                <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined text-lg\">${t.icon}</span>\n                <span class=\"font-bold text-sm\">${t.label}</span>\n            </div>`).join('');\n\n        document.getElementById('historyList').innerHTML = db.history.map(h => `\n            <div class=\"flex items-center justify-between py-3 group cursor-pointer border-b border-zinc-200\">\n                <div class=\"flex items-center gap-4\">\n                    <div class=\"w-10 h-10 flex items-center justify-center bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl group-hover:bg-primary/10 transition-colors\">\n                        <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined text-secondary group-hover:text-primary\">history</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <span class=\"font-semibold text-lg tracking-tight\">${h}</span>\n                </div>\n                <span class=\"material-symbols-outlined text-secondary hover:text-primary\">north_west</span>\n            </div>`).join('');\n\n        document.getElementById('curatedGrid').innerHTML = db.curated.map(c => `\n            <div class=\"relative h-40 rounded-3xl overflow-hidden bg-zinc-900 group cursor-pointer\">\n                <img referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer\" src=\"${c.img}\" class=\"w-full h-full object-cover opacity-60 group-hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-700\">\n                <div class=\"absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/80 to-transparent p-6 flex flex-col justify-end\">\n                    <p class=\"text-primary font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-1\">${c.category}</p>\n                    <h3 class=\"text-white font-bold text-xl\">${c.title}</h3>\n                </div>\n            </div>`).join('');\n            \n        await window.forge.db.set('kinetic_editorial_search', 'default', db);\n    }\n\n    async function clearHistory() {\n        let db = await window.forge.db.get('kinetic_editorial_search', 'default');\n        db.history = [];\n        await window.forge.db.set('kinetic_editorial_search', 'default', db);\n        init();\n    }\n\n    async function exportCSV() {\n        let db = await window.forge.db.get('kinetic_editorial_search', 'default');\n        const csv = \"Recent Searches\\n\" + db.history.join('\\n');\n        const a = document.createElement('a');\n        a.href = 'data:text/csv;charset=utf-8,' + encodeURI(csv);\n        a.download = 'searches.csv';\n        a.click();\n    }\n\n    init();\n</script>\n<footer class=\"text-center p-4 text-neutral-400 text-xs opacity-80 flex justify-center items-center gap-1.5 mt-auto\"><span>Built with</span> <img src=\"https://forge-app.vercel.app/logo.png\" alt=\"Forge\" class=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 rounded-sm object-cover\"> <a href=\"https://forge-app.vercel.app\" class=\"text-blue-500 font-semibold tracking-wide no-underline\">FORGE</a></footer>\n</body>\n</html>",
